The paper deals with the problem of constructing codes that can correct deletions in a string, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The encoding and decoding algorithms involve manipulating the string, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial constructions of codes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The optimal redundancy of the codes is a key concern, which is a topic in complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the problem of constructing codes that can correct deletions in a string has applications in computational geometry (cs.CG).
